<h2>Setting Up AngularJS</h2>

Terminal
 touch index.html
  creates a new file named index.html
 open .
  opens the current directory
  
Download AngularJS 1.6 <a href="https://angularjs.org/">here</a> 

Adding the CDN
'''<script src='js/angular.min.js'></script>'''

<h2>Emulating a Hosting Server</h2>

Angular: Single-page app (more fluidity)

Terminal
  python -m SimpleHTTPServer
  Go to Chrome
    Enter 127.0.0.1:8000 OR localhost:8000 OR 0.0.0.0:8000
   

